Sanauarola putteth the degrees of the coldnes, which the yron hath, and sayeth;
   Sanauarola.
 that it is colde in the seconde degree, and dry in the third. B. Maister Doctor I pray you to passe forwarde: for vnto mee, that which is spoken, is sufficient, for I haue no doubt therof, but that the yron is colde and dry, and alwayes I haue vnderstood it to be so, and now with the confirmation of such authors, I holde it for more certaine and firme. D. Maister Burgus hath very quickly
